{
  "stem": "8610.3",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But to, to think of people being thrown into a, a living-- a wide-open furnace, as it were, and being, being gassed by the-- being closed in a chamber and, and gassed by throwing this Zyklon gas through the-- through the-- some channel or other, you can't visualize it.",
      "word_count": 49
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You can't visualize it.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I never saw a gas chamber, I must admit.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But, but, but I can now visualize it, having seen what corpses are like, what hunger is like, and what disease is like.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I can still see a picture in my mind of bodies being slung into, into this camp-- dreadful, dreadful thought, slung into mass graves of bodies.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "There was no-- the-- I'm used to burials.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I'm used to officiating at a funeral, where the body is dignified.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The coffin is put in, lowered in the ground, and so on.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But to take a skeleton and chuck it in with no dignity, then where is the, the personality?",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Gone.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The so-called human image disappears.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "This is a-- this is a horrible picture that remains with you still.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And when I see these pictures that are being reproduced-- as they are periodically, and they probably will be for God knows how many years to come-- there-- it all comes back very vividly.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I say to myself, you've seen it on the screen.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It's nothing compared with reality.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And when my dear friend, Lord Bernstein, who came over to Belsen shortly after liberation with an official team of cameramen-- and he took a film.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And his idea was that he would show this film.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "He actually got local German officials to come and watch the bodies being buried, thrown into-- [SIGHS] the British authorities wouldn't allow that film to be shown.",
      "word_count": 27
    }
  ],
